1.1483 

General arbitrage rebate rules. 


* * * * * 


(j) ***





Example 1. Calculation and payment of rebate for a fixed 
yield issue. 

(i) 

Facts. 

On January 1, 1994, City 

A 

issues a 
fixed yield issue and invests all the sale proceeds of the issue 
($49 million). There are no other gross proceeds. The issue has 
a yield of 7.0000 percent per year compounded semiannually 
(computed on a 30 day month/360 day year basis). City 

A 

receives 
amounts from the investment and immediately expends them for the 
governmental purpose of the issue as follows: 


